main event: A bright, white, oblong-shaped object was observed over Spangdahlem Air Base in Germany on February 25, 1961.
interesting points: The object was described as almost pure white in color, oblong in shape, and appeared similar to a large, bright star.
The object was observed moving in different directions, sometimes approaching the observation tower and sometimes moving below the cloud ceiling.
The object was visible for approximately 6 minutes and disappeared on a heading of 255 degrees.
No trail, sound, or other distinguishing features were observed.
Weather conditions at the time included ground fog, scattered and broken cloud cover, and good visibility.
